\pard\f0\fs28   {\b P. villarsii} R. Schulz, {\i Monogr. Phyteuma} 143 (1904), from rock-crevices in the mountains of S.E. France and N.W. Italy, has slender, decumbent stems and more numerous, grey-green leaves, with deeper, unequal teeth. The middle cauline leaves are truncate or shortly cuneate at base. It has 2n = 26.
\par 

