\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 22. P. globulariifolium} Sternb. & Hoppe, {\i Denkschr. Bayer. Bot. Ges. Regensb.}{\b  1}({\b 2}): 100 (1818) ({\i P. pauciflorum} auct., non L.). Stock much-branched. Stem 1-12 cm, erect, glabrous, with few or no leaves. Basal leaves numerous, rosulate, obovate to oblanceolate or rarely linear-elliptical, narrowed into the petiole, widest near the apex; cauline leaves similar; all leaves glabrous or ciliate, obscurely crenate-serrate, with the apex not projecting beyond the uppermost pair of teeth, or entire. Inflorescence 2-to 7-(-12)flowered, globose. Outer bracts orbicular to ovate or all, or the inner only, lanceolate, acuminate to obtuse, sometimes crenate at the apex, ciliate, shorter or longer than the inflorescence. Corolla deep blue-violet, curved in bud. Stigmas 3.{\i  Rocks and screes; calcifuge. • Alps and Pyrenees.} Au Ga He Hs It.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   Polymorphic. The following treatment is only provisional as further study, particularly of subsp.{\i  pedemontanum,} is needed.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b globulariifolium}: stem 1-5 cm; leaves obtuse, often crenate towards the apex. Outer bracts suborbicular, often wider than long, obtuse. 2n = 28.{\i  E. Alps, westwards to} c. 10° 30'{\i  E}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b pedemontanum} (R. Schulz) Becherer,{\i  Denkschr. Schweiz. Naturf  Ges.}{\b  81}: 417 (1956) ({\i P. pedemontanum} R. Schulz): stem 5-12 cm; leaves acute, often 3-dentate at apex, longer than in subsp. ({\b a}). Outer bracts more or less lanceolate shortly acuminate. 2n = 28.{\i  Pyrenees and Alps, eastwards to} c. 11° {\b E}.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   Connected with subsp. ({\b a}) by numerous intermediates in the eastern part of its range. In the S. part of the S.W. Alps variants with longer stems and leaves seem to approach {\i P. hemisphaericum} var. {\i platyphyllum}. They may represent a vicariant taxon of{\b  24}.
