\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 24. P. confusum} A. Kerner,{\i  Zeitschr. Ferdinand.} ({\i Innsbruck}) ser. 3, {\b 15}: 247 (1870). Like {\b 22}({\b a}) but stem 1-15 cm; leaves linear to oblong-spathulate, usually more or less abruptly narrowed to the usually regularly serrulate or crenulate, obtuse base and apex, the apex projecting well beyond the uppermost pair of teeth; bracts orbicular to ovate, entire or sometimes with few small teeth in the distal part; corolla dark blue-violet, rarely white. 2n = 28+0-1B.{\i  Rocks and stony pastures; calcifuge. • Mountains of E.C. & S.E. Europe southwards to C. Bulgaria.} Al Au Bu Ju Rm.
